# Axis 18 — nearest matching reset

`.ssc` realizes multi-prompt delimited control through algebraic effects with deep
handlers: nested `handle` boundaries for the same effect are nested `reset`s. A `shift`
— an operation whose handler discards its continuation — is caught by the NEAREST
enclosing reset. Here the inner reset catches the shift and returns 7; the surrounding
`+ 1000` sits in the inner reset's answer position and yields 1007, which the outer
reset (which would also match the shift, but never sees it) passes through.

```scalascript
effect Ctl:
  def shift(): Int

def prog(): Int = handle {
  val inner = handle {
    Ctl.shift()
  } {
    case Ctl.shift(resume) => 7
  }
  inner + 1000
} {
  case Ctl.shift(resume) => 7
}

println(prog())
```
